== Per-file SPDX semantics ==

Each first-party source file in hipfire carries an SPDX-License-
Identifier reflecting the actual authorship of that file:

    Apache-2.0               File's substantive authors (>= 30% of
                             lines per `git blame`) are all in the
                             set of authors who have opted into
                             Apache-2.0 for hipfire going forward,
                             currently {Kaden Schutt, Kevin Read}.

    MIT                      File's substantive authors are all
                             outside the Apache-2.0-opt-in set. The
                             contributor's original MIT grant is
                             preserved as-is. If they later opt in,
                             the SPDX tag is refreshed by re-running
                             scripts/governance/apply_spdx_headers.py
                             --rewrite-spdx after the opt-in is
                             recorded.

    MIT OR Apache-2.0        File has substantive authors on both
                             sides of the opt-in boundary. The dual
                             tag is the conservative default until
                             the non-opted-in author elects which
                             grant applies to their portion.

A small number of license-administration files created in the
relicense work itself (e.g. scripts/governance/apply_spdx_headers.py)
are explicitly Apache-2.0.

